<br>
My advice is to choose a diety too.  My first and second wizzies were agnostic which was just fine but that was before all the cool equipment came out.  (1st and 2nd wizzies were Corinia on Nameless server.  She's still there with her eq and everything.)  I say stay erudite.  My newest and longest wizzy follows Quellios and in all honesty, he's more of a cleric/pally god but I enjoy roleplaying how I started following him.  (Wizzy I play is Renia on Cazic-Thule.)<br>
<br>
Lexicons are basically found in any wizard guild.  They're in Erudin, Qeynos, Felwithe, POK.  You just have to look at the guys who sell things in your guild.  I never did the research quests.  I just dove into researching my spells.<br>
<br>
I believe in the do it yourself way in getting levels and equipment.  As for equipment you need, learn tailoring and make silk stuff for yourself until you can upgrade.  Deal with the meditating.  Earn your kit, don't buy it.  But this is me.<br>
<br>
I realize that you have a lot of pp so you probably do things the faster way and can go buy yourself stuff.  Go to the bazaar, bring up the bazaar screen and look for wizard usable plus int stuff at the lower levels.  For mana, go to the Nexus or POK and buy C3's - donate between 20-50pp.  Do not jip the chanters.  They will remember.  If you donate, they will sometimes give you freebies later when you need them.  Try not to die after you get the C3.  Sometimes enchanters will drive by clarity or C3 you.  Personally I don't think that up until level 30 should you really need c3s but I do notice people getting them.  Other than that, flowing thought items will make your mana regen faster.  Those are expensive but can be found in the bazaar.<br>
<br>
My advice would be to look up the Staff of the Wheel quest on Allakhazam's and do it at level 20.  It takes you all over Norrath and you learn a lot while traveling.  You also could die, so be prepared.  And, it's a mighty fine beginning staff.<br>
<br>
Good luck.  I love being a wizzy and I hope you enjoy it. <p>Renia - wizardess of Cazic-Thule<br>
