<br>
The easiest place for you to find a Lexicon would probably be Erudin Palace.  There is a vendor on the third floor of the Erudin Palace wizard guild (which I assume you're familiar with) who sells them, along with parchments and quills.  Be aware, though, that this lexicon only works to research spells up to level 49.  Beyond that, you need one of the new lexicons, which can be gotten for free by talking to one of the NPCs in the Gulf of Gunthak, on the little lighthouse island right as you zone in.  I forget his name and exact location now, though.  This new lexicon will, from what I recall, also work to research lower-level spells, so you may just want to get that one.<br>
<br>
For gear, you may want to browse the Equipment section of these forums, there are several helpful threads.  In terms of specific pieces of gear, I found the polished bone bracelet and/or the bracelet of woven grass to be helpful; both are relatively cheap, and have int and a handy focus effect.  One thing I would highly recommend is to do the quest for the fine antique ring:  <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2193">everquest.allakhazam.com/...quest=2193</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
You can probably find all the quest pieces for cheap in the bazaar, or on NPC vendors.  It shouldn't leave your finger until level 49 at least.<br>
<br>
Practically speaking, there are probably only a couple items with mana regen realistically available to you, and those are probably hideously expensive.  The best thing to do is to pay for a KEI in the nexus or PoK.  If you are friends with a sub-60 enchanter, you can probably just bum a breeze (hey, it's better than nothing), clarity, or clarity II off them, depending on their level.  Likewise with beastlords and spiritual light, etc.<br>
<br>
I hope that helps.  Good luck in your journeys!<br>
